27/02/2004
ORESTIADA, Greece -- Greek, Turkish and Bulgarian prefects met on Thursday (26 February) in Orestiada, northern Greece, to discuss cross-border co-operation. 
Present at the meeting were Nikolaos Zambounidis of Evros, Greece, Fahri Yugel of Edrine, Turkey and Georgi Zarchev of Haskovo, Bulgaria. 
The meeting was held within the framework of creating a network of border region provinces that would foster multilateral co-operation on a regional level. 
The prefects will meet again next month to adopt an official charter. 
(ANA - 26/02/04)
